  <title>Gio.PropertyAction.new</title>
  <synopsis><code mime="text/x-gjs">
function new(name: String, object: void, property_name: String): <link xref="Gio.PropertyAction">Gio.PropertyAction</link> {
    // Gjs wrapper for g_property_action_new()
}
  </code></synopsis>
  <p>Creates a <link xref="Gio.Action"/> corresponding to the value of property
<code>property_name</code> on <code>object</code>.</p>  <p>The property must be existent and readable and writable (and not
construct-only).</p>  <p>This function takes a reference on <code>object</code> and doesn't release it
until the action is destroyed.</p>
  <p>Since 2.38</p>
